values: So I found out today that my friend Holly had a really bad roommate situation down in LA.  A girl left, didn't pay her rent, and everyone got kicked out because the landlord was a dick.  Holly is now moving in my room with me, and in a few months we are moving to LA together!!!!!  This is going to be a shockingly crazy change!  LA here I come

A few days ago I was playing with his dog Slick, and I said Slickers what am I going to do without you?  Dean quickly retorted that he had already offered the roommate position to me but, it would have to be completely pleutonic.  I told him we can hardly do that now, and I am nowhere near ready to do that to myself.  I have come to a point where I am at a loss for what to do.  His Bar exam is tuesday through thursday, I am taking care of his dog for that time.  After he is done with the Bar I am he is going to be reintroduced to the wild where undoubtedly he will be with Colin most of the time.  I am so hurt right now that I can't understand my own feelings let alone his.  I know I can't let myself hurt forever, but that is what feels like is going to happen.  I know it was my mistake and I shouldn't have doubted us in the first place, but I am content in the fact that I know where my feelings stand for him.  Through misunderstanding and turbulent times we have come to this plateau.  There is no right nor wrong choice for either of us and the only thing that bonds us is our past combined with emotions.  I can't let this keep going it isn't healthy for me.  I need him to make this less painful and either put me out of my misery or save me from myself.  The more time passes I can't help but lose him.  I am crying...I have to stop

The update...so here is what I am/have been thinking about the last few weeks.  After I returned from England I got back together with Dean.  I have been in love with him since I met him. I got back and we hung out a few times.  I told him if he is dating me then he is dating only me.  After a brief period he agreed.  Things were going swimmingly until I realized how little of him I was actually seeing.  I knew he was busy with school, but I just wasn't getting enough.  I went to Boy Bar (A club/bar in the Castro) with him, and he introduced me to what I fondly refer to as the "Slew of Hookers".  These people being the ones who would come into my store and be completely rude and act as if they were better than every person around them.  I told Dean I had to leave.  Instead of staying with his friends like I told him to, he took me home.  I proceeded to tell him how I felt.  He said he would try harder, and that he didn't care about those people...they were his MySpace friends.  A week and a half went by and by, and then I met this guy named Matt.  He came up to me on the sidewalk and said what is a cute guy like you doing alone.  I told him I was waiting for my manager.  I told him that I was seeing Dean and he said no pressure, just friends.  So I hung out with him.  He started telling me about how he would treat me if I was with him, an yadda yadda ya.  This sparked a fury in me.  Why was it so hard for me to get my bf to tell me these things, but a stranger could walk up on the street and after three days tell me what I should have.  I went to Dean and I hurt him.  I told him I wasn't getting enough, and that I needed someone who really cared.  We had a four hour convo in which we broke up and got back together four times.  I spent the night.  I didn't hear from him for two days.  I called him and told him that I didn't want to distract him from the Bar.  That I wasn't going to be blamed for him failing if it came down to it.  He agreed and we decided to  seperate.  I decided to not see Dean or Matt for a while.  I started talking to Matt again because I knew he was moving.  I helped him move to his new place and paint it.  I started talking to Dean again.  Dean took a trip to Sacramento to get away and study.  He left with more than knowledge.  He decided he wanted to date a boy named Colin.  I told Dean when I got a hold of him that I realized what I lost.  That I love him so much that I wanted to fall off the earth with him, and only be his.  I was at a point where I was giving myself fully to him.  He said we would talk when he got back.  We did.  He told me about Colin, and that I was being a child and not making proper decisions to which I fully agreed.  He said it was too late...I cried.  I have cried oh, just about every day.  Maybe I have gotten away without crying for one, but I was sure as hell thinking about it.  Oh, forgot to mention, Colin is going to school 20 minutes away from where Dean will be working in LA.  I am doomed.  I care so much for him that I want to see him happy, but it turns my stomach to think of them together.  I better not do this all in one posting, I will continue on the next one.

Wow...I hadn't actually realized that I hadn't finished my London story...I have pictures to send anyone to tell the story!  There was too much to type.  Overall good time, decided I can't move to London.  I quit my clothing store, and I have started at Bong Su, a Vietnamese French fusion restaurant.  I am going to be working there part/full time as an assistant pastry chef.  More to come, and perhaps it won't take three months before I get on here again...oh and I died on MySpace.  It was getting to me, so I deleted it...yeah

This morning Arbury, Alan, Jonathan and I woke up and began a wonderous journey.  One that involved force-feeding Arbury chicken fingers while she was driving.  We learnt Arbs some macro-economics...hmm then it was off to England for Seany!  I arrived at the airport and there were no delays!!!  I stepped on the plane and right into my seat!  There were some super hot hotties!  I fell asleep, which never happens, and the stuerdess smacks me with a pair of headphones...that is where it all started buh buh buh!  The Flight From Hell!  I could not fall back asleep.  The girl who hit me kept saying you look tired...fucking bitch...  SO, I watched two movies played sudoku for an hour then I ran my iPod battery down til the end of the flight...we hit airpockets yadda ya...I get off the plane and onto the Underground...mind you I haven't done this in 6 months!  I arrive at Holborn Station, and I get my bag stuck in the gates to leave the building.  Luckily I had saved enough battery to have my iPod blasting so I couldn't hear the guy saying let go of your bag, you are going to break the gate!!!  Alarms went off it was great :)   to be continued...
How can one person make another person's heart so badly?

If that isn't the darndest thing I ever saw
You Are 28 Years Old
Under 12: You are a kid at heart. You still have an optimistic life view - and you look at the world with awe. 13-19: You are a teenager at heart. You question authority and are still trying to find your place in this world. 20-29: You are a twentysomething at heart. You feel excited about what's to come... love, work, and new experiences. 30-39: You are a thirtysomething at heart. You've had a taste of success and true love, but you want more! 40+: You are a mature adult. You've been through most of the ups and downs of life already. Now you get to sit back and relax.
What Age Do You Act?

I am fairly sure that I am completely crazy now!  The day we got into London we met up with Matt's friend Paul.  Super hot!  As we were walking down the stairs of this coffee shop, Matt turned to me and said, oh btw Paul's friend David is here!  The last thing I needed was to be set up with a troll from a different country!  So I was pissed!  We meet him, and he is so gorgeous!  Wow!!!  We go get some drinks, hang out, flirt, it was great!  Paul had to go to work, so I told David he couldn't possibly leave us alone in such a huge city.  SO HE STAYED :)  He dropped us off at an Underground station and that was that!  The next day, Paul calls, wants to hang out, David's there!  WE saw him every night right up until New Years!  He was my date!  We went to this club that was called PopStarz!  It was amazing, we danced all night, did poppers, got tossed before we even went!  It was great, we had the most amazing time.  At midnight, he kissed me, and it was the best kiss I have ever had, it even topped my first which was my cherished one!  He told Matt he thought I was cute, yadda yadda ya, I fell so hard for him!  I have been a wreck ever since.  On the first night we met two acqauintances of David's.  Australian and Lithuanian.  I we saw them again at G-A-Y the club.  I said hi, we talked a bit, he asked Matt if he liked Paul, he said yes, he turned to me and asked if I liked David and I said yes!  Australian talked to Lithuanian, who talked to Michael (not sure the affiliation of this one) but he told David.  Apparently David is like my brother and only wants what he can't have, so he is not interested now.  Here is the best part, I can't stop thinking about him, and we are hanging out with him tomorrow night!  I have to talk to him!  YIKES!  I sent him a drunken e-mail on Myspace the other day.....he read it today.....I don't know what he is thinking.....who has one of those amphibious cars that would like to get me the hell out of JOLLY OL' ENGLAND!!!!!!!!!!!!!   HEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEEELLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLLP

Not sure whether or not this is a happy or sad post, I guess you could call it melancholy, but that is a little pretentious....Anywho, so many feelings at once...

Matt was a dick, but now he is acting like he really cares for me.  I am not sure what to take from this as he sure didn't seem like it last time.  He wants me to spend New Years with him in England....I want to go...I think I love him...and when I finally learn that I am wrong I will end up being in a wonderful city that I can discover on my own...I have my plan...I have my backup...I know that I would be an emotional hurricane but I can deal....

My parents are showing how much they care about my feelings, which I knew they always cared, but I didn't know that they cared that much.

I have great friends down here.  I really am starting to feel an attachment towards them.  I am glad to know them.  At first I thought it was a lil Postal Servicey of me and this place was a prison and these people weren't my friends but they do care.

I am growing....

Once on a high pedestal our hero now hangs by a thread...that thread being close close close friends and family.  These close kin allow our hero to survive off the mere thought that there are at least a few who care...very few anymore however...

Prereq. Story

     So last weekend Hone came.  Judging by some of my recent entries you would most likely assume this was a joyous event....you are sadly mistaken...  From the moment of arrival something fishy was in the air.   I believe this was stemmed from the fact that one of our more important phone calls he stated in a dream that we were just good friends...not together.  Well, we arrived home and settled in.  Diego was introduced, and we all hung out in the living room.  After the awkward intro, we arrived at the idea that we were all hungers...so we went to Little Italy to a lovely bistro called the Mona Lisa.  In a rousing round of boring how do you do convo Hone decides to ask some questions...
"Who would you want to be?"
"Who would you want to meet?"
"Who would you want to fall in love with you and marry you?"
     As the last question fell on me I paused, if I say Hone I will be embarassed...if I say i celeb I will wish I had said Hone...  I asked him if he meant celeb...or...what?  He said it could be either one, whatever I felt....I didn't answer :(

Wow...Just had a thought...I am way too tired for the rest of this story...this is going to be a long entry so just hang in there....Soon to be Finished!

Not only is my cake going to be the same size (three tiers) but it is going to be exactly the same cake!!!  Fuck you Chef!  I liked you but now I loathe you!

I got ready and headed over, we did warm-ups which were ok, until we did climbs....I did 3-4 climbs (go as high as you can with your arms and feet) on both the aerial rope and aerial tissue, I burned the fuck out of my hands and by the time we learned falls I was too tired so I had to learn how to do them from 1 foot off the ground...

All in All a very shitty day.....................................but....................................Hone comes friday!
